<br>
Does 200hp really make you 3 percent better at tanking?  That depends on what you are tanking.  The whole point of having a massive hp pool is to reduce the chance of you being one rounded to an acceptably low level.  Once you have enough hp so that you can keep the risk of being one rounded below 2 or 3 percent and your guild's CH cycle can keep you up comfortably, additional hp provide very little benefit.  They might only reduce the chance of you dieing by a tenth, or even a hundredth of a percent.  In fact, if you have enough hp to survive maximum punishment from a mob for the length of time between 2 CHs in your guild's best sustainable CH chain, then additional hp provide you with no value.  On the other hand, if you have a lower hp total relative to the amount of damage the mob can put out, those 200 hp might be a 50 percent improvement in tanking ability or more.<br>
<br>
The other issue is aggro generation.  Several people has mentioned the notion of holding aggro well-enough.  The combination of your procs and your damage form the aggro curve that your entire guild has to stay under.  If you can raise your damage by 16 percent, then you have just boosted the whole raids ability to deliver damage.  Granted, dps while defensive is utter @#%$, and adding 16 percent to utter @#%$ is not much of an improvement.  However, you will spend a fair portion of each big fight not in defensive.  During those periods 16 percent more damage would be a great help in pushing up your aggro curve and thus helping the raid up its DPS.<br>
<br>
More DPS is helpful nearly all the time.  The marginal value of 200 hp varies greatly.  I would like the option of having both around to tailor to the situation. <p><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5309"target="_blank"alt = "Korak's Megalo Profile"><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR = 10,10,900><b>Korak Sarathai - Barbarian Warlord - The Hand</b></FONT><BR></a><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12530"target="_blank"alt = "Dumesh's Megalo Profile"><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR = 900,10,10><b>Dumesh Uhl'Belk - Retired Troll Reaver - The Hand</b></FONT><BR></a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udumeshuhlbelk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dumesh UhlBelk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://personal.atl.bellsouth.net/bhm/w/i/wilsonua/Eye.bmp" BORDER=0> at: 10/8/02 10:57:21 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usinark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinark</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 322<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/8/02 11:27:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2189.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_atk.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: dps v hps</span><hr size=1> Yeah, I totally agree. It's not nearly as simple as that, but I was just using his numbers to make a point. <br>
<br>
I think you underestimate the value of an extra 200hps though. I guess if you always use the same quickest possible CH cycle and it's always perfect, then yeah extra hps won't help in a lot of cases. But what you're missing is that when you have substantially more hps, you can get away with slower CH cycles with fewer clerics. The extra hps also let you survive the inevitable mistakes, fizzles, lag, mistargets and all the other things that can cause a cycle to fart for a few seconds.<br>
<br>
On the other side, I maintain that my damage output has a negligible impact on my ability to hold aggro. EB procs make up the vast majority of my aggro. So you're not really adding 16% to your aggro, you're adding 16% to whatever small % of your aggro that damage makes up. Keep in mind that there a couple of fights in game where the MT routinely does zero damage and still holds sufficient aggro. <p><html>
